The paper proposes a method for Neural Architecture Search (NAS) to automatically produce deep networks with excellent performance and acceptable computational costs. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of a performance predictor, which is a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
